      • getInputCollectionRdds

        public Map<String,org.apache.spark.api.java.JavaRDD<SimpleRecord>> getInputCollectionRdds()
        Deprecated. 
        Get all Koverse input collection RDDs from the parameters that were input by the user. The key of the map is the parameter name and the value is the RDD for the input collection for that parameter. None of the keys or values in the returned map will be null. The returned map will be immutable. Note that the partitioning of the RDDs will be based on the batch size that your Koverse server is configured to use. In some cases, you may get much better performance by repartitioning these RDDS to a higher number of partitions. Exactly how many partitions to use is highly dependent on your algorithm and may require experimentation to get the best performance.
        Returns:
        Koverse input collection RDDs from the parameters parameters that were input by the user.
        See Also:
        getParameters()
